text: Brocchinia kaiensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae, the nutmeg snails. ==Description== ==Distribution== This marine species occurs in the Arafura Sea, off Indonesia. ==References== * Verhecken, A., 1997. Mollusca Gastropoda: Arafura Sea Cancellariidae collected during the Karubar Cruise. Mémoires du Muséum national d'Histoire naturelle 172: 295-323 ==External links== * MNHN, Paris: holotype Category:Cancellariidae Category:Gastropods described in 1997
title: Brocchinia kaiensis
